---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="DataBreef uses only strictly necessary cookies for session management. No advertising, no cross-site tracking."
  lastUpdated="April 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains what cookies DataBreef uses, why we use them, and what choices you have.
    We keep it simple: DataBreef uses the minimum cookies required to function, and nothing more.
  </p>

  <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser when you visit a website. They
    allow the site to remember information about your visit — like whether you are logged in — across
    page loads and sessions.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>

  <h3>Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies are required for DataBreef to function. They cannot be disabled without breaking
    core features of the service. We do not require consent for these cookies under most privacy
    frameworks because they are essential.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Session cookie</strong> — Stores your authenticated session token so you remain logged in
      as you navigate the application. Expires when you close your browser or after 30 days if you select
      "Remember me."
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>CSRF token</strong> — A security token that protects form submissions from cross-site
      request forgery attacks. Session-scoped; expires with your session.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Auth state cookie</strong> — A short-lived cookie used during the OAuth authentication
      flow (GitHub, Google) to prevent state forgery. Expires within 15 minutes.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Preference Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    DataBreef may set a preference cookie to remember UI choices such as your selected pricing
    billing period (monthly/annual). These contain no personal data and expire after 90 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies We Do NOT Use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Advertising or retargeting cookies</li>
    <li>Cross-site tracking cookies</li>
    <li>Analytics cookies from third-party providers (e.g., Google Analytics)</li>
    <li>Social media tracking pixels</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not share cookie data with advertisers or data brokers. Ever.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    DataBreef does not embed third-party widgets, ad networks, or social share buttons that would
    set their own cookies on our marketing pages. Stripe's payment flow, accessed only when
    upgrading your plan, may set their own cookies governed by
    <a href="https://stripe.com/cookies-policy/legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stripe's Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling strictly necessary
    cookies will prevent you from logging in to DataBreef. Most browsers allow you to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>View and delete existing cookies</li>
    <li>Block cookies from specific sites</li>
    <li>Block all third-party cookies</li>
    <li>Clear all cookies when you close your browser</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we introduce new cookies or change how we use existing ones, we will update this page and,
    where required by law, seek your consent before setting any new non-essential cookies.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-contact">
    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>Cookie questions? Contact us at:</p>
    <p><strong>DataBreef</strong> — <a href="mailto:privacy@databreef.io">privacy@databreef.io</a></p>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
